            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">32.006-5</ph> Reporting.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d2009e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2023e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            In accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.4506(h)</xref>, the head of an agency, other than the Department of Defense, shall prepare a report for each fiscal year in which a recommendation has been received pursuant to <xref href="FAR-i1083564.dita#i1083564"
                        base="i1083564"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">32.006-4</xref>(a). Reports within the Department of Defense shall be prepared in accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2307(i)(7)</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2023e35" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            In accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.4506(h)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2307(i)(7)</xref>, each report shall contain-</p>
					          <ol id="d2009e47" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2023e51" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Each recommendation made by the remedy coordination official;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2023e60" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The actions taken on the recommendation(s), with reasons for such actions; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2023e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                An assessment of the effects of each action on the Government.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
